title: Grateful Dead Live at Hampton Coliseum on 1989-10-09
description:
Set 1

Feel Like A Stranger, Built To Last, Little Red Rooster, Ramble On Rose, We Can Run But We Can't Hide, Jack A Roe, Memphis Blues, Row Jimmy, The Music Never Stopped

Set 2

Playin' In The Band-> Uncle John's Band-> Playin' In The Band Reprise, Dark Star-> Drums-> Jam-> Death Don't Have No Mercy-> Dear Mr. Fantasy-> Hey Jude Reprise-> Throwing Stones-> Good Lovin', E: Attics Of My Life

reviews.review_text: Wow, Hampton. lol, grew up in norfolk, va. Spaceship thanks man. It seems that SB shows, or of "SB qualitysound" shows, are becoming un-downloadable. I was 8yr's old in '89. Been an archive guy since my early teens. Its the sound, we need to have these shows. So peep younger than I can "get it". It was beautiful, I remember. Hearing a show that was an SB record. I FELT it, and hope our world continues to FEEL and GET the GD. Peace, Adrian

Formerly The Warlocks Who are these guys called The Warlocks?
they sound JUST like the Dead!
love how the crowd goes apeshit when they play Dark Star for the first time since 84 and Attics since 72
great DDHNM also
bobby ruins the Hey Jude outro, but hey, just skip to the next song.

To all hater’s Look I was late to the game I know but this is one of the best Brent and Jerry shows of the time. If you were lucky enough to be there consider yourself lucky blessed. Remember there are people out there who don’t have the numbers under their belt to speak about anything. Guess what that’s me I don’t know anything my first and only show was the last show. It changed my life and if I listen to all the hater’s in life I would have never seen or been to the places I’ve been to. Do like you were hopefully taught if you don’t have anything positive or good to say don’t say anything at all. People are very impressionable when they are looking for guidance guess what we’re all here to teach and guide our job is to shed light not to master so out of your horrible experience find the one most stupidest thing possible and make it positive. Us peps who know no better might take your statement as a100% real deal. Not for me but different strokes for different folks all that needs to be said. What you choose to do on your own time is on you. Peace love and happiness. Go see see shows so someday you can leave a positive statement and encourage not discourage people on your beliefs
